Estimated number of one-year-olds who have received vaccinations for different diseases.
Data source: UN, World Population Prospects (2024); WHO & UNICEF (2024)

Note: This includes
diphtheria
,
pertussis
and tetanus (3rd dose), measles (1st dose),
hepatitis B
(3rd dose), polio (3rd dose), Haemophilus

influenzae b (3rd dose), rubella (1st dose),
rotavirus
(final dose), yellow fever (1st dose), and
inactivated polio
(first dose).
